ink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-TCX4hGolAc8\/XZQIOMFryQI\/AAAAAAAAcQo\/spnTub6rQfUYnhBhE0Y17eBXHZsBHE_eQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_zP8D_sb-wI9hPbEW.png","title":"Southern-Style Fried Chicken & Sweetcorn","publishedAt":"2018-02-19T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"13.5 g","fat":"35.8 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"25 g","calories":"1979 kJ \/ 473 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray, large frying pan, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Heat vegetable oil until shimmering but not smoking. To test temperature, carefully lower a small piece of bread into the oil, it should sizzle and turn golden. This is best done with a frying thermometer, the correct temperature should be between 180°C and 190°C.","For a gluten-free version, substitute plain flour for gluten-free cornflour.","For spicy fried chicken sprinkle with paprika or chilli powder, a squeeze of lemon and a pinch of extra salt.","The corn mixture can also be tossed through pasta with grated Parmesan and an added pinch of black pepper for a light summer lunch."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","55m","4 portions"]}